-25/√6650 -56/√6650 |   |  2 |\n\nQ^T * b = |  38/√38  |\n          |  19/√6650 |\n          |-104/√6650 |\n\nNow we can solve the upper triangular system Rx = Q^T * b using back substitution:\n\n1. x = (38/√38) / (1900/√6650) = 38*√6650 / 1900 = 19/50\n2. y = ((19/√6650) - (1900/√6650) * (19/50)) / (6650/√6650) = 19/6650\n3. z = (-104/√6650 + (1900/√6650) * (19/50)) / (1900/√6650) = -104/1900\n\nSo the solution to the system of linear equations is:\n\nx = 19/50\ny = 19/6650\nz = -104/1900"
